result.execSummary:
The defendant Tracy Lee Turner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Business Setting >$10,000 [Modifiers: Penalties for Felonies-Class "G" Felony], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, DA: Michael Edward Nieskes, DF ATTY: Frederic W Knaak, DF: Tracy Lee Turner appeared.  Court called.  Court questions the attorneys as to if they had reviewed the PSI.  All parties have reviewed it.  No objections to it.  State makes their recommendation.  State is in agreement with the DOC recommendation in the PSI.  DA Nieskes makes his argument to sentencing. Crt orders:

Ct. 1 
S/W 3 years probation with conditions
- Comply with any programming recommended by the COMPAS and DOC
-  DE ordered to have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, All American Title Company and their employees.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, social media including but not limited to texting, Facebook, Twitter, contact through the mail, and/or through a third person. 
- DE is ordered to complete Restorative Justice and a Victim Empathy Seminar
- DE to provide the St. Croix County Jail with a DNA sample
- Court costs of $268.00 and $250.00 for the DNA surcharge to be paid through the department of corrections
- DE to sign up for probation by 02/28/17 by 5:00 p.m.
- 20 days to appeal

It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations,  All American Title Company in Hudson WI.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as no contact in person, by telephone, by way of electronic device, email, facsimile, through the mail, and/or through a third person.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ORDERED that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis. Stats.
